    <item>
      <title>Robin Relocates - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Jun 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13481" class="post-13481 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Robin Relocates&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Today, I received my bug trophy in the mail, from winning the Bug-Off last weekend. I sold it for 2,450 bells, which is more than I expected it to be worth.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I visited Robin, I saw that she is moving out of town&amp;#8230;and spreading her wings. 😆 Maybe she saw the Bat Signal in the sky, and she has to fly.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Robin: I just HAVE to spread my wings, so to speak. But I'm glad I saw you before I left, la-di-da! Take care!" class="wp-image-13482" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m okay with her leaving; I do still have her in Wild World, after all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Back outside, Felicity called me crazy for being up so late&amp;#8230;even though it was only 8 p.m.! But then she realized that she was still up too, so she must be the crazy one. Either that, or everyone else.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Felicity: But I'm up, too... So that means that I'M the crazy one... Or maybe it's just everyone else!" class="wp-image-13483" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Biskit was talking about K.K. Slider being at the Roost tonight. But he also was talking about going over there tomorrow to hear a song at lunchtime? K.K. won&amp;#8217;t still be there tomorrow, dawg!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Biskit: I'm thinking of going over there tomorrow and requesting a good song with my lunch!" class="wp-image-13484" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But speaking of the Roost, I did head over there myself. Monty was in there too, enjoying some coffee.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Monty, at the Roost: The coffee here is rich and mysterious, much like myself." class="wp-image-13485" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I asked K.K. for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. House&amp;#8221; for me and Monty.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. House." class="wp-image-13486" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It&amp;#8217;s not a bad song; the chorus is the &lt;em&gt;key&lt;/em&gt;, and now it lives &lt;em&gt;rent-free&lt;/em&gt; in my head. 🏠😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was raining in town tonight, and Rosie was sick of the dampness. She even said if hating rain is bad, she wants to be REALLY bad. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/Array" alt="Rosie: Boooo! If hating the rain is bad, then I wanna be REALLY bad!" class="wp-image-13487" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Nana was sick with a cold today, so I gave her some medicine. Get well soon, monkey brain.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;July starts next week (Tuesday, in fact), and that means prime bug-hunting season is almost here! I&amp;#8217;m wrapping up June with 67,650,000 bells in savings. My summer goal will be to earn 2.35 million more bells, so that I reach 70 million bells by September 1st. That shouldn&amp;#8217;t be a problem with the way I enjoy my summer bug-hunting nights. 🙂 I&amp;#8217;ll also post a video of one of those sessions at some point in July, too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Good luck with your bug hunting everyone, and I&amp;#8217;ll see you in July! 🦋&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/06/28/robin-relocates/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-06-28T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;June 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-06-29T00:36:11-04:00"&gt;June 29, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/RUU_8271-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>June Bug-Off 2025 - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 29 Jun 2025 03:21:08 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8840" class="post-8840 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;June Bug-Off 2025&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, Pascal popped up in the rain to talk about yoga poses.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Pascal: Downward-facing dog might be a yoga pose, maaan, but upward-facing otter is a way of life." class="wp-image-8845" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Bob sent me this letter on Wednesday, along with a gift. He found it under his bed while looking for candy, and he wondered if it was a piece of toffee&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Hey, boss! I was looking for a piece of candy I dropped under my bed and found this. It's hard as a rock! I'm pretty sure it's not the candy I dropped. Unless it turns out to be a toffee bar...then it is and I want it back. -Toffee-love Bob" class="wp-image-8846" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But the attached item was actually coprolite. That&amp;#8217;s fossilized dino poop! Wow, he&amp;#8217;s lucky he didn&amp;#8217;t lick it to taste what it was! Yuck! 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, I dug up the daily glowing spot money, and then a zigzag pattern led me to three of the day&amp;#8217;s four fossils! That was four of the five buried items all in one area.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="395" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="A zigzag pattern led me from the glowing spot to three of the day's fossils!" class="wp-image-8844" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Bones, he told me to pick a color. He said he would tell me what food I&amp;#8217;m most like. I picked red, and he compared me to a &amp;#8220;hababa-ben-erioh&amp;#8221; pepper. He&amp;#8217;s wrong, of course, but I thought it was cute how he struggled to pronounce habanero. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Bones: Red! That means you're fiery like a hababa-ben-erioh pepper! One taste of you and everybody's jumpin'!" class="wp-image-8847" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I know some of you have had issues with Joy-Con drift, and I&amp;#8217;ve been having issues with Pro Controller drift for a while. I sometimes don&amp;#8217;t get the full amount of bells from money rocks, because the controller wants to move my character down. And the problem is getting worse, too. The other day, I walked into Nook&amp;#8217;s shop and my character left the store by himself! 😆 It&amp;#8217;s annoying, but I don&amp;#8217;t want to buy a new Pro Controller when I&amp;#8217;ll be getting Switch 2 within the next few months.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, the June Bug-Off was held, and I participated in one round. But as I was trying to catch a drone beetle, Static was in my way and I kept talking to him by mistake!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="Static: Kiddo, this here's a bug-catchin' contest, not a jaw-flappin' contest. Get back in there and compete!" class="wp-image-8848" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But despite the setback, I still ended up catching 14 bugs&amp;#8230;which was good for 16 points.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/Array" alt="I caught a common bluebottle!" class="wp-image-8849" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I sold my 14 bugs to Flick for 4,110 bells, and then I redeemed ten of my points for a bug wand.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Due to the Bug-Off, there was no K.K. Slider concert tonight. Here are a few other quick notes about the past week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Last Saturday, K.K. performed &amp;#8220;Marine Song 2001&amp;#8221; for me, Ketchup, Peanut, Agent S, and Bones.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Ketchup was sick on Sunday, so I gave her some medicine. In return, she gave me an attus robe.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Tuesday, I helped out Wisp and he gave me a portable record player.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, I had a &lt;em&gt;whale &lt;/em&gt;of a fishing day; I caught &lt;strong&gt;three &lt;/strong&gt;whale sharks! And also a great white shark, a saw shark, and a coelacanth! 💰💰💰&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I helped out Gulliver; he sent me a tubeteika in the mail today.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I recently posted my latest New Horizons Moments video. Check it out!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="New Horizons Moments #34 (Animal Crossing)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7wRWNN9OaDM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/06/28/june-bug-off-2025/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-06-28T23:21:08-04:00"&gt;June 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-06-28T23:23:03-04:00"&gt;June 28, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/pascal-downward-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Friends are Watches? - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Jun 2025 03:56:58 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8215" class="post-8215 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Friends are Watches?&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;When I played on Wednesday, I received a letter from Curt in the mail. At first, I thought that meant he moved out, but that wasn&amp;#8217;t the case this time. There is one other reason a villager will send you a letter: When they have a birthday coming up. He invited me to his birthday party on July 1st, and I thought this letter was pretty funny:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Hey there, Jeff, I'll be one year older on July 1st! So come to my place for cake and some sad jazz music. COME! From, Curt" class="wp-image-8216" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I don&amp;#8217;t often play on Tuesdays, but I&amp;#8217;ll try to make an exception next week (if I remember).&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over by town hall, I listened in on a conversation between Whitney and Filbert. Whitney was taking a personality quiz, and she asked if I wanted to take it too. She asked what role a wristwatch plays in my life, and I chose &amp;#8220;convenience.&amp;#8221; She said watches symbolize friendship, so Filbert jumped in and said that according to me, &amp;#8220;friends are just watches.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Filbert: So according to you, bunny, friends are just watches." class="wp-image-8217" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Filbert and Whitney both got mad at me, for something I never said! Whitney even called me a big unfeeling robot. I wanted to &lt;em&gt;clock &lt;/em&gt;them both. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Filbert: I don't get you! At all!" class="wp-image-8219" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Whitney: You think Filbert is a watch?! YOU'RE JUST A BIG, UNFEELING ROBOT!" class="wp-image-8218" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And to think, these are (or were?) my two favorite villagers in town! And they ganged up on me to attack me for something so harmless. This might be the most unhinged conversation I&amp;#8217;ve seen in Animal Crossing yet. So unnecessarily mean-spirited.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Curt was telling me that it&amp;#8217;s not cool to rummage through villagers&amp;#8217; stuff. But as he did, he referenced the &amp;#8220;population growing,&amp;#8221; which is on the sign on the cover of the first Animal Crossing.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Curt: It's all fine and good that the population of Forest is growing..." class="wp-image-8221" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It was raining, and Truffles was afraid the rain was going to turn her into Truffles soup! Yuck, I think I&amp;#8217;d rather have some &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nFIa6I5lVrk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;hot ham water&lt;/a&gt;. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Truffles: But this rain will turn me into Truffles soup in, like, two seconds flat!" class="wp-image-8222" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Robin asked me for a new catchphrase, so I told her to say &amp;#8220;on a pizza.&amp;#8221; Admittedly, it isn&amp;#8217;t the most logical catchphrase&amp;#8230;like it would be for Anchovy. But I&amp;#8217;m hoping the randomness of it will spice up Robin&amp;#8217;s dialogue a bit.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Robin: Yes, I, too, salute career ladies everywhere! After all, I am one, on a pizza!" class="wp-image-8223" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Robin: Eeeek! OK, Robin, don't cry! It'll mess up your mascara! On a pizza!" class="wp-image-8224" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline&amp;#8217;s sickness has continued into its &lt;em&gt;third week&lt;/em&gt;! 😮 I gave her more medicine Wednesday and yesterday. By today, she was finally over her cold! She thanked me for the medicine and gave me some slate flooring.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Caroline: Here you go! Consider my slate flooring all yours, stop it." class="wp-image-8226" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After three weeks, I was wondering if she&amp;#8217;d ever get over that cold. Well, better &lt;em&gt;slate &lt;/em&gt;than never. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Pascal was down on the beach today, and he told me some words of wisdom before handing me some sea view wallpaper.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array" alt="Pascal: You only scrape your feet if you dwell on the bottom, maaannn." class="wp-image-8225" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/06/27/friends-are-watches/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-06-27T23:56:58-04:00"&gt;June 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-06-27T23:56:59-04:00"&gt;June 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/curt-letter.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Rainy Season - Jeff&amp;#039;s Animal Crossing Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Jun 2025 03:02:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-5972" class="post-5972 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Rainy Season&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;When I played on Monday (June 23rd), I received a goodbye letter from Lulu in the mail. So long, Lulu!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="To Jeff, I'm leaving town, and I'm not telling anyone where I'm going, but don't you worry! I'm off on a grand adventure that's totally going to rule! Wish me luck in my new life. Don't forget me! -Lulu!" class="wp-image-5974" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Puck suggested we play a game, and all I had to do was pick left or right. I agreed to play, and I picked &amp;#8220;right.&amp;#8221; But then he forced me to buy a kitschy clock from him for 2,170 bells!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Puck: Looks like you're buying a kitschy clock for 2,170 bells, brrrrrrrrr!" class="wp-image-5975" style="width:450px;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Now wait just one &lt;em&gt;second&lt;/em&gt;!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He never even said the game would involve a purchase; that&amp;#8217;s not a game to me! That &lt;em&gt;ticked &lt;/em&gt;me off. I ought to &lt;em&gt;clock &lt;/em&gt;him! &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was raining in town, but Maple was trying to convince herself that she only felt humid because it was all in her mind. She thought that if she remembered that it&amp;#8217;s June, she&amp;#8217;ll be nice and dry? I don&amp;#8217;t follow her logic at all, but I didn&amp;#8217;t want to dampen her enthusiasm.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Maple: I just need to remember that it's June, and I'll be nice and dry!" class="wp-image-5976" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Belle told me that the sound of raindrops makes her sleepy&amp;#8230;and then right on cue, she fell asleep standing up. Luckily for her, I didn&amp;#8217;t tip her over. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Belle: Listening to the sound of raindrops always makes me sleepy, cuddles." class="wp-image-5977" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I wasn&amp;#8217;t holding an umbrella myself, and Kody thought that made me pretty stupid. Thanks, pal.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Kody: You may be brave, but you're also pretty stupid! It's not healthy, Jeff!" class="wp-image-5978" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;In the southwest corner of town, I met my newest villager, Puddles. Even though she&amp;#8217;s a frog, she couldn&amp;#8217;t wait for it to stop raining.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Puddles: Aw! I wish the rain would hurry up and stop, splish!" class="wp-image-5979" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;What&amp;#8217;s up with that? She&amp;#8217;s literally named after a byproduct of rain. 🌧️&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over by the wishing well, Baabara tried to convince me that it was the exact moment that spring changed into summer.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Baabara: I'll have you know, this is the exact moment when spring changes into summer." class="wp-image-5980" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I asked why, and she said it was because Sydney caught a beetle already. That&amp;#8217;s not how seasons work, and even if it was, &lt;em&gt;that &lt;/em&gt;would have been the exact moment. Not the moment that Baabara tells me about the beetle. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I played again today, and it was raining once again. Static was his usual cheery self, threatening to release the hounds on me. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Static: No! I'm not interested! Go away, bzzzt! Don't make me release the hounds on you!" class="wp-image-5981" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Chill out, Mr. Burns.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Belle was sick of all the rain lately, as was I. I&amp;#8217;m ready for the rainy season to end already!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Belle: It feels like it's been raining all the time lately. I hate getting wet!" class="wp-image-5982" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After a brief chat about muscle cramps, my best buddy Hank gave me a No. 1 shirt as a token of our friendship. Aww. 🙂&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Hank: How about I give you this No. 1 shirt for free, okey-dokey! Enjoy it! It's a token of friendship!" class="wp-image-5983" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Of course, I put the shirt on right away.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Down by the ocean, I found Gulliver washed up on the beach. He told me his story of how he ended up in the sea.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="450" height="346" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/Array" alt="Gulliver: I jumped over the railing and into the ocean! The thing is, I don't know how to swim. I had forgotten that..." class="wp-image-5984" sizes="auto, (max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;To reward me for helping him, he gave me a tiger bobblehead. I guess that&amp;#8217;s &lt;em&gt;claws &lt;/em&gt;for celebration. 🐅 Having earned my stripes, I headed home and wrapped up my game for the day. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I hope to see you all next time! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2025/06/26/rainy-season/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-06-26T23:02:38-04:00"&gt;June 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/ac-lulu-out2025-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Summer Solstice 2025 - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Jun 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18247" class="post-18247 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Summer Solstice 2025&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Lolly&amp;#8217;s catchphrase has continued to provide some entertaining moments in recent weeks.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Lolly: Big events are great, but I enjoy everyday life too. It gives me the chance to unwind, if I poop." class="wp-image-18248" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Lolly: A perfect peach is a rare treat, so keep your eyes peeled for them, if I poop!" class="wp-image-18249" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rolf also asked for a new catchphrase last week, so I told him to say &amp;#8220;at death.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Rolf: I'm gonna take it out for a test drive, but I'm pretty sure I just found my new thing, at death!" class="wp-image-18250" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Rolf: I knew I could count on you! Stay awesome, at death!" class="wp-image-18251" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;That might be hard to do, but I&amp;#8217;ll try. 😛&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today was the Summer Solstice, the day of the midnight sun. I played about 10:30 p.m., but as you can see, it was still bright and sunny. I headed over to the event plaza to get my gift from Isabelle&amp;#8230;except Isabelle looked a bit different today.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Nat stands near the face-cutout standee for the summer solstice." class="wp-image-18252" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The Bug-Off was also held today, so that explains Nat&amp;#8217;s appearance at the plaza. But still, where was Isabelle? I was confused. Regardless, I stuck my face in the cutout hole for a photo. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Look, I'm a flower!" class="wp-image-18253" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But moments later, everything made more sense. I found Isabelle standing outside of town hall!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Isabelle stands outside of town hall for an event." class="wp-image-18254" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It felt weird seeing her here for an event! But I spoke with her, and she gave me some ladder shades. 😎&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Isabelle: Hello, Mayor! Today is the Summer Solstice! It's also the day of the big Bug-Off! Perfect day for both!" class="wp-image-18255" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The indoor villagers were talking about the Summer Solstice, and Hornsby wondered if dinner should still be called dinner.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Hornsby: There's no night today, so does it still make sense to call dinner dinner?" class="wp-image-18256" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Hornsby: I think I'm gonna call it lunch the second! Yeah, that sounds good!" class="wp-image-18257" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And my outdoor villagers were talking about the Bug-Off. But since I didn&amp;#8217;t play between the hours of 6-9 p.m., the awards ceremony was cancelled. Boots and Jeremiah were bummed out about that.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Boots: Aw, barbells! The Bug-Off awards ceremony was canceled!" class="wp-image-18258" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Jeremiah: I can't believe it! The awards ceremony was canceled." class="wp-image-18259" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;This may be nitpicky, but this is one small thing I hate about New Leaf. Animal Crossing has always pushed the idea that town life goes on whether you&amp;#8217;re playing or not. So to cancel an event just because I didn&amp;#8217;t play within a specific three-hour window annoys me. I did see on the bulletin board that Inkwell won the event with a 41-point bug, but there&amp;#8217;s no reason to guilt players who missed the ceremony.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Anyway, I put on my ladder shades and posed for one last photo of the night. Have a bright night, everyone! ☀️&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/Array" alt="Isabelle stands near town hall and the geyser erupts and I stand near a yellow bench and tulip topiary." class="wp-image-18260" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/06/21/summer-solstice-2025/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-06-21T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;June 21, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-06-22T00:02:58-04:00"&gt;June 22, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/20250611_HNI_0063.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
